b'' b'' b' the prozac gave very bad anxiety/jitters and insomina, it was impossible to' b' sit still for more than a minute or so.' b'' b'i tried prozac a few months ago, and had some insomnia from it, but no' b'anxiety or jitters. i probably could have lived with the insomnia if the' b'prozac had done any good, but it only provided a tiny benefit. maybe' b"because the person who prescribed it didn't know much and gave up after a" b"20mg dose didn't work." b'' b"now i'm seeing a psychiatrist who has put me on zoloft (another serotonin" b'reuptake inhibitor like prozac). one pill/day (50mg) seemed to help some.' b"now i'm trying 100mg/day. zoloft has fewer and milder side effects than" b'prozac. i think my doctor said that only of the people taking zoloft' b"have to discontinue it because of side effects. the only problem i'm" b'having is some minor gi distress, but nothing too annoying. hopefully the' b'zoloft will work. maybe your friend should try this one next.' b'' b"my psychiatrist's strategy seems to be to first try one of the serotonin" b'drugs, usually prozac. if that works, great. if it works but has too many' b"side effects, try zoloft or maybe paxil. if the serotonin drugs don't work" b'at all, try one of the tricyclics like desipramine.' b'' b'...suggestions as to the next step?' b'' b'having a doctor who knows something about antidepressants can make a big' b"difference. my psychiatrist claims that most gps and fps don't have much" b"experience in this area, and from what i've seen i'm inclined to believe" b'him. i think i know more about antidepressants than the people at my' b"family practitioner's office." b'' b"disclaimer: i'm not a doctor; what i know about this comes from talking to" b'my psychiatrist and reading sci.med.' b'' b'--' b'uc berkeley school of education 